      <h2>Pricing</h2>

      <div class="pricing-info">
        <div class="pricing-tier free">
          <h3>Free Tier</h3>
          <ul class="pricing-features">
            <li>100,000 requests per day</li>
            <li>Unlimited CPU milliseconds (but still capped by request timeout)</li>
            <li>10ms CPU time included daily</li>
            <li>All Workers features included</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="pricing-note">Perfect for hobby projects and learning.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="pricing-tier pro">
          <h3>Pro Plan</h3>
          <ul class="pricing-features">
            <li>\$5/month base</li>
            <li>Unlimited requests</li>
            <li>\$0.50 per 1M CPU milliseconds</li>
            <li>All features</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="pricing-note">Scales from hobby to enterprise.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="pricing-example"><strong>Example:</strong> 10M requests/month with 50ms average CPU time = 500M ms √ó \$0.50/1M = \$250/month (vs \$2,000+ with traditional servers).</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Limitations -->
  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Limitations to Be Aware Of</h2>

      <div class="limitations">
        <div class="limitation">
          <h3>30 Second Timeout</h3>
          <p>Each request has a maximum 30-second timeout. Use Durable Objects for longer operations.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="limitation">
          <h3>128MB Script Size</h3>
          <p>Your uploaded script (including dependencies) has a 128MB limit. Optimize bundle size.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="limitation">
          <h3>Memory per Isolate</h3>
          <p>Each isolate instance has memory constraints. Design for stateless operation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="limitation">
          <h3>Node.js Compatibility</h3>
          <p>Workers use V8 isolates, not Node.js. Some npm packages may not be compatible.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="limitation">
          <h3>No Persistent Storage (Within Request)</h3>
          <p>Use KV Store or Durable Objects for persistence. Don't rely on local file system.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="limitation">
          <h3>Billing Concerns</h3>
          <p>High CPU-intensive operations can get expensive quickly. Monitor and optimize.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Clodo Matters -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why Clodo Makes Workers Better</h2>

      <p>While Cloudflare Workers is powerful, it has a steep learning curve. Clodo simplifies everything:</p>

      <div class="clodo-benefits">
        <div class="benefit">
          <h3>üöÄ Instant Setup</h3>
